  "accepted_findings": [
    "Per-tile transparent RGB padding restores strong olive-green response in the retained near, mid, and runtime-far crown geometry.",
    "The correction changes only RGB at alpha <=2, while alpha and all nontransparent source RGB remain byte-for-byte identical by recorded hashes.",
    "Normal and packed texture source files retain their pre-padding hashes, isolating the correction to albedo mip filtering.",
    "The source correction is deterministic, project-owned, tile-bounded, regression-tested, and retained for later foliage passes."
  ],
  "rejection_reasons": [
    "Four-times opacity still saturates card coverage and produces dense solid crown masses instead of leaf-shaped distance breakup.",
    "River-eye crown pixels remain 61.34 percent dark despite the large green-response improvement.",
    "The corridor still contains only one dominant species family and lacks riparian understory, deadwood, mixed canopy, and ecology review.",
    "Coarse terrain, provisional water, sparse placement, temporal wind, and packaged desktop/VR gates remain open."
  ],
  "next_iteration_requirements": [
    "Capture alpha scales 2 and 3 with the corrected atlas, neutral 1.18 reflectance, native TwoSidedFoliage, and leaf shadows disabled.",
    "Choose the lowest opacity scale that preserves registered near/mid/far crown continuity while restoring leaf-edge breakup.",
    "Then reintroduce bounded leaf shadows with contact-shadow controls and verify that elongated ground carpets do not return.",
    "Repeat both corridor views before adding a second ecology-reviewed native canopy stratum."
  ]
